Sentencas: Solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) are of great importance in terms of reducing operational costs and benefiting from system durability.
Titulo: Heterogeneous Composite Fibrous Cathode Undergoing Emphasized Active Oxygen Dissociation for La(Sr)Ga(Mg)O3-Based High-Performed Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: However, SOFCs exhibit sluggish oxygen reduction reactions (ORRs) at cathodes.
Titulo: Heterogeneous Composite Fibrous Cathode Undergoing Emphasized Active Oxygen Dissociation for La(Sr)Ga(Mg)O3-Based High-Performed Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: To overcome this, extensive research is focused on the development of cathodes with superior ORR properties for SOFCs.
Titulo: Heterogeneous Composite Fibrous Cathode Undergoing Emphasized Active Oxygen Dissociation for La(Sr)Ga(Mg)O3-Based High-Performed Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: In this study, a fibrous composite cathode composed of strontium-doped samarium cobaltate (SSC) and samarium-doped ceria (SDC) is fabricated via electrospinning.
Titulo: Heterogeneous Composite Fibrous Cathode Undergoing Emphasized Active Oxygen Dissociation for La(Sr)Ga(Mg)O3-Based High-Performed Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Composite fiber cathodes prepared at specific ratios exhibit ORR properties and oxygen-ion conductivity, which are attributed to the growth of small SSC particles in the fibrous electrode and nanolattice strain of SSC at the SSC and SDC interface.
Titulo: Heterogeneous Composite Fibrous Cathode Undergoing Emphasized Active Oxygen Dissociation for La(Sr)Ga(Mg)O3-Based High-Performed Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: As such, the enhanced cathode performance contributes to an improvement in the power-generation characteristics of SOFCs (1.33 W cm(-2) at 1073 K using 300 mu m thick La(Sr)Ga(Mg)O-3 electrolyte).
Titulo: Heterogeneous Composite Fibrous Cathode Undergoing Emphasized Active Oxygen Dissociation for La(Sr)Ga(Mg)O3-Based High-Performed Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: This structural engineering of dual-phase fiber is a promising design that promotes cathodic ORR performance.
Titulo: Heterogeneous Composite Fibrous Cathode Undergoing Emphasized Active Oxygen Dissociation for La(Sr)Ga(Mg)O3-Based High-Performed Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
